52.7	Oldboy	Oldboy	Oldboy (Hangul: ; RR: ; MR: , the phonetic transliteration of "old boy") is a 2003 South Korean film directed by Park Chan-wook. It is based on the Japanese manga of the same name written by Nobuaki Minegishi and Garon Tsuchiya. Oldboy is the second installment of The Vengeance Trilogy, preceded by Sympathy for Mr. Vengeance and followed by Sympathy for Lady Vengeance.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/67/Oldboykoreanposter.jpg/220px-Oldboykoreanposter.jpg
